1
00:00:03,505 --> 00:00:05,174
[♪]

2
00:01:04,895 --> 00:01:06,597
[♪]

3
00:01:09,902 --> 00:01:11,671
MAN:
<i>Tobio.</i>

4
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:14,275
<i>Tobio.</i>

5
00:01:14,309 --> 00:01:16,512
BOY:
<i>I'm here! Hello?</i>

6
00:01:18,848 --> 00:01:21,853
SCIENTIST:
Capacity passing 80 percent.

7
00:01:23,889 --> 00:01:27,794
SCIENTIST 2:
Tobio's neural network
is beginning to respond.

8
00:01:27,828 --> 00:01:29,697
[MACHINES WHIRRING]

9
00:01:36,975 --> 00:01:38,810
Almost there.

10
00:01:38,844 --> 00:01:40,380
You can do it.

11
00:01:41,815 --> 00:01:44,686
BOY:
I can't see you. Where are you?

12
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:01,310
Come on! Increase power!

13
00:02:01,343 --> 00:02:03,446
We can't.
We're at maximum now.

14
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,850
We need more! Call the
Magnamite power station.

15
00:02:05,884 --> 00:02:07,953
Have them bring
all reserves on line.

16
00:02:07,987 --> 00:02:10,323
Sir! That much
energy would--

17
00:02:10,357 --> 00:02:11,926
Tell them it's on my authority.

18
00:02:11,959 --> 00:02:13,761
I'll take personal
responsibility.

19
00:02:13,796 --> 00:02:15,865
This is too important
to fail now.

20
00:02:15,899 --> 00:02:18,335
He's almost charged.

21
00:02:25,312 --> 00:02:27,982
Emergency orders
for Magnamite.

22
00:02:28,016 --> 00:02:29,084
Activate all reserve stations

23
00:02:29,118 --> 00:02:32,689
and reroute all power
to the Ministry of Science.

24
00:02:32,723 --> 00:02:34,459
That would exceed
safety parameters.

25
00:02:34,492 --> 00:02:38,297
Nonsense. Magnamite's job is
to send power where we say.

26
00:02:38,331 --> 00:02:39,666
Now, give it the order.

27
00:03:07,407 --> 00:03:08,809
Ah, yes.

28
00:03:11,446 --> 00:03:13,849
The very same move I made.

29
00:03:13,883 --> 00:03:16,988
O'SHAY:
<i>Come on, Tobio. Wake up.</i>

30
00:03:17,021 --> 00:03:20,058
BOY:
<i>I see you now!</i>
<i>I'm coming toward you!</i>

31
00:03:24,966 --> 00:03:27,036
No!

32
00:03:27,069 --> 00:03:29,840
SCIENTIST:
Doctor, don't!
It's too dangerous!

33
00:03:34,113 --> 00:03:36,416
Get back to
your posts now.

34
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:37,952
We've come...

35
00:03:39,821 --> 00:03:43,392
too close to be stopped
by a loose cable.

36
00:03:45,996 --> 00:03:47,432
[GRUNTS]

37
00:03:48,935 --> 00:03:49,769
Huh?

38
00:04:02,821 --> 00:04:04,423
[♪]

39
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,801
Huh?

40
00:04:35,636 --> 00:04:38,874
O'SHAY:
Hello, Tobio.

41
00:04:38,908 --> 00:04:42,045
No, that's not right.
This is your new life.

42
00:04:42,078 --> 00:04:44,682
I think you should have
a new name.

43
00:04:44,716 --> 00:04:47,019
Uh, how about...? Um...

44
00:04:48,788 --> 00:04:51,692
Astro.

45
00:04:51,726 --> 00:04:54,597
Welcome to the world, Astro.

46
00:04:56,634 --> 00:04:58,202
ROBOT:
Sir, systems
returning to normal,

47
00:04:58,236 --> 00:04:59,904
but there's been
a relay imbalance.

48
00:04:59,938 --> 00:05:01,507
Eight thousand megawatts
went into Magnamite

49
00:05:01,541 --> 00:05:03,710
that never came out.

50
00:05:03,744 --> 00:05:05,847
ADMINISTRATOR:
What do you mean,
"never came out"?

51
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,816
Where did the power go?

52
00:05:17,197 --> 00:05:19,267
If even half the rumors
are true--

53
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:21,536
This robot's
a technological marvel.

54
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:24,775
And with some kind
of new artificial intelligence.

55
00:05:24,808 --> 00:05:26,143
And weapons.

56
00:05:28,780 --> 00:05:29,948
ALL:
Huh?

57
00:05:29,982 --> 00:05:31,551
Oh, good, you're here.

58
00:05:31,585 --> 00:05:34,789
Gentlemen, I'd like you
to meet Astro,

59
00:05:34,822 --> 00:05:39,629
the most evolved robot
science has ever created.

60
00:05:39,662 --> 00:05:42,601
You're kidding, right?
It looks like a child.

61
00:05:42,634 --> 00:05:44,904
Can it even
do anything?

62
00:05:44,937 --> 00:05:46,707
Don't let his look fool you.

63
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:48,810
He's learning
at an exponential rate.

64
00:05:48,843 --> 00:05:51,179
And he has <i>kokoro,</i>
his own thoughts and spirit.

65
00:05:51,213 --> 00:05:53,617
MAN:
Right.

66
00:05:53,650 --> 00:05:55,553
Call us when it's learned
something useful.

67
00:05:55,586 --> 00:05:56,821
Like how to sweep up.

68
00:05:59,158 --> 00:06:02,730
Wait! Think of the future!

69
00:06:02,763 --> 00:06:05,134
ASTRO:
Come in for a landing.
There's a clearing.

70
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,869
Ooh.
Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha.

71
00:06:06,902 --> 00:06:09,139
Now he talks.

72
00:06:09,173 --> 00:06:12,778
Excuse me. Dr. O'Shay?
Uh, Yuko.

73
00:06:12,811 --> 00:06:16,183
You're scheduled to return
phone calls from 1 to 2.

74
00:06:16,216 --> 00:06:19,855
You're already
40 seconds late.

75
00:06:19,888 --> 00:06:22,993
Fine. Nora, start Astro
on his lessons.

76
00:06:23,026 --> 00:06:24,695
Leave it to me,
sir.

77
00:06:24,728 --> 00:06:26,898
Nothing too difficult, now.
Uh...

78
00:06:26,931 --> 00:06:28,233
Please, doctor.

79
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:30,136
O'SHAY:
Okay, okay.

80
00:06:30,170 --> 00:06:32,173
Be good, Astro!

81
00:06:34,142 --> 00:06:37,113
Ready?
Lesson one: obedience.

82
00:06:37,146 --> 00:06:38,816
Whoa! What's that?

83
00:06:40,351 --> 00:06:42,855
NORA:
Hey! You're not
paying attention!

84
00:06:42,889 --> 00:06:44,191
Stop!
I'm in charge here.

85
00:06:45,426 --> 00:06:47,395
Oh, please.
Oh, please be careful.

86
00:06:47,428 --> 00:06:49,865
Oh, Dr. O'Shay will dismantle me
if you're damaged.

87
00:06:53,004 --> 00:06:55,107
I'm supposed to be learning,
right?

88
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:58,277
Yes, and I'm supposed
to be teaching.

89
00:06:58,311 --> 00:07:00,781
NORA:
Stop!

90
00:07:00,815 --> 00:07:02,984
Oh, my circuits can't take it!

91
00:07:03,018 --> 00:07:06,289
ASTRO:
Don't blow a gasket.
I'll be right back.

92
00:07:07,257 --> 00:07:09,761
[CRASH]

93
00:07:09,794 --> 00:07:13,199
ADMINISTRATOR:
We've been getting strange
readings from Magnamite all day.

94
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,036
It's malfunctioning.

95
00:07:15,069 --> 00:07:17,773
And the police were just here.

96
00:07:17,806 --> 00:07:19,976
<i>They wanted to know</i>
<i>about the power outage,</i>

97
00:07:20,009 --> 00:07:22,079
so I sent them to you, doctor.

98
00:07:22,112 --> 00:07:23,882
<i>I was only</i>
<i>following your orders,</i>

99
00:07:23,915 --> 00:07:26,052
<i>and I'm not</i>
<i>taking the blame for this!</i>

100
00:07:26,919 --> 00:07:28,856
[SIGHS]

101
00:07:28,889 --> 00:07:32,094
MAN: I'm here to see Dr. O'Shay.
Huh?

102
00:07:32,127 --> 00:07:34,197
Wait. You can't just
go in there.

103
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:36,167
I'm Detective Tawashi,
Metro City Police.

104
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:39,838
I demand an explanation
for your citywide blackout!

105
00:07:39,872 --> 00:07:42,276
I can't sleep
with the lights on?

106
00:07:42,309 --> 00:07:44,812
[GROANS]

107
00:07:44,845 --> 00:07:46,982
[♪]

108
00:07:56,229 --> 00:07:57,831
Wow!

109
00:07:57,864 --> 00:08:01,404
Now, these are toys.

110
00:08:02,872 --> 00:08:05,142
Hey, wait up.
Give me a lift.

111
00:08:07,546 --> 00:08:09,381
[LAUGHING]

112
00:08:12,553 --> 00:08:15,224
A robot that thinks for itself?

113
00:08:15,257 --> 00:08:17,760
That's right.
It's called <i>kokoro.</i>

114
00:08:17,794 --> 00:08:20,264
He has emotions, compassion,
a mind of his own.

115
00:08:20,297 --> 00:08:24,037
If it acts on its own,
then it could be dangerous.

116
00:08:24,070 --> 00:08:26,974
Astro's not an "it,"
and <i>he</i> always behaves.

117
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,877
You sure about that?
I'm positive!

118
00:08:28,910 --> 00:08:30,279
[ASTRO SCREAMING]

119
00:08:30,312 --> 00:08:31,481
Astro!

120
00:08:34,084 --> 00:08:36,254
Astro!

121
00:08:42,329 --> 00:08:43,899
Astro!

122
00:08:43,932 --> 00:08:44,466
[SCREAMING]

123
00:08:51,076 --> 00:08:51,843
Oh, no!

124
00:09:02,293 --> 00:09:03,961
Hey!

125
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:08,568
Whoa!

126
00:09:09,336 --> 00:09:11,172
I can fly!

127
00:09:11,206 --> 00:09:13,342
Woo-hoo!

128
00:09:16,079 --> 00:09:17,981
[LAUGHING]

129
00:09:22,555 --> 00:09:23,524
Hey!

130
00:09:23,557 --> 00:09:24,558
Oof!

131
00:09:26,027 --> 00:09:28,063
Ah, looks delicious.

132
00:09:28,096 --> 00:09:29,498
[SCREAMING]

133
00:09:33,939 --> 00:09:35,141
ASTRO:
Oh, no!

134
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:39,413
[GRUNTING]

135
00:09:40,448 --> 00:09:41,883
Look!
A balloon!

136
00:09:43,419 --> 00:09:45,021
Children!
Children!

137
00:09:51,230 --> 00:09:53,367
Yeah.
Not bad for a first flight.

138
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,335
Huh?

139
00:09:58,675 --> 00:09:59,943
You missed one.

140
00:09:59,977 --> 00:10:00,911
Hm?

141
00:10:04,383 --> 00:10:05,418
Hey!

142
00:10:18,203 --> 00:10:21,341
O'SHAY:
Yuko, you and Nora check
the park. I'll look downtown.

143
00:10:21,374 --> 00:10:24,145
I don't want that Detective
Tawashi to find him first.

144
00:10:24,178 --> 00:10:25,114
[SIRENS WAILING]

145
00:10:27,583 --> 00:10:29,019
You heard me.

146
00:10:29,052 --> 00:10:31,423
A flying robot
that looks like a kid.

147
00:10:31,456 --> 00:10:35,061
ROBOT:
Error. Magnamite is rejecting
reroute instructions.

148
00:10:35,094 --> 00:10:37,164
Send in the maintenance robots.

149
00:10:37,197 --> 00:10:40,702
See if the power overload
blew one of its circuits.

150
00:10:49,349 --> 00:10:51,552
ROBOT:
It's destroying
the maintenance bots! Emergency!

151
00:10:57,261 --> 00:11:00,431
ASTRO:
Wow. Check it out.

152
00:11:00,465 --> 00:11:02,134
Awesome.

153
00:11:12,316 --> 00:11:13,484
Yeah!

154
00:11:14,652 --> 00:11:15,653
Excuse me.

155
00:11:23,799 --> 00:11:26,069
ADMINISTRATOR:
It's detaching itself
from the grid.

156
00:11:26,103 --> 00:11:28,072
Emergency response
to Metro Power!

157
00:11:28,106 --> 00:11:30,475
Magnamite is totally
out of control!

158
00:11:36,251 --> 00:11:38,120
Wrap exactly 10 meters of cable

159
00:11:38,153 --> 00:11:40,189
onto your spool.
Hey!

160
00:11:40,223 --> 00:11:41,391
Can I spin him?

161
00:11:41,425 --> 00:11:42,693
Stop.
Do not come closer.

162
00:11:42,727 --> 00:11:44,830
Why not?

163
00:11:44,863 --> 00:11:47,834
By order of Metro City.
Oh, it looks like fun!

164
00:11:47,868 --> 00:11:51,272
This is not a game.
This is work.
Oh.

165
00:11:51,306 --> 00:11:53,443
"Work"?
What do you mean, "work"?

166
00:11:53,476 --> 00:11:55,646
Work is what robots
are programmed to do,

167
00:11:55,679 --> 00:11:59,251
and every robot has a purpose.

168
00:11:59,284 --> 00:12:01,354
A purpose?

169
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,256
Whoa!

170
00:12:02,289 --> 00:12:04,124
Ahh!

171
00:12:04,158 --> 00:12:06,762
Stand back. There's something
wrong with the power grid.

172
00:12:11,569 --> 00:12:14,306
<i>Magnamite has stopped</i>
<i>following our orders.</i>

173
00:12:14,339 --> 00:12:16,710
<i>It's broken loose</i>
<i>and is moving on its own.</i>

174
00:12:16,743 --> 00:12:19,213
Dr. Tenma must've sabotaged it.

175
00:12:19,246 --> 00:12:21,316
He knew what I'd need to do.

176
00:12:21,349 --> 00:12:24,188
Have you tried a full reboot?

177
00:12:24,221 --> 00:12:26,191
ADMINISTRATOR:
<i>It's too late for that.</i>

178
00:12:26,224 --> 00:12:27,593
<i>Magnamite's climbing</i>
<i>out of the plant.</i>

179
00:12:27,626 --> 00:12:29,128
<i>We can't control it!</i>

180
00:12:29,161 --> 00:12:30,129
[CHUCKLING]

181
00:12:53,797 --> 00:12:57,269
This is my fault.
I have to do something!

182
00:12:57,302 --> 00:12:59,239
YUKO:
<i>Just be careful, doctor.</i>

183
00:13:21,537 --> 00:13:24,842
Yuko, tell the police.
It's heading into the city.

184
00:13:26,812 --> 00:13:28,882
[O'SHAY GRUNTING]

185
00:13:30,384 --> 00:13:31,186
Huh?

186
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,836
[SCREAMS]

187
00:13:48,611 --> 00:13:50,347
[♪]

188
00:13:51,048 --> 00:13:52,249
Help! Help!

189
00:13:56,556 --> 00:13:57,524
Doctor?

190
00:13:57,557 --> 00:13:58,525
Yes, please.

191
00:13:58,559 --> 00:13:59,493
Gotta fly!

192
00:14:04,434 --> 00:14:05,869
Get away! Get away! Get away!

193
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:14,983
ASTRO:
Gotcha!

194
00:14:25,831 --> 00:14:28,836
You're safe now, doctor.
You wait here.

195
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:30,272
Astro!

196
00:14:32,575 --> 00:14:33,843
[SIRENS WAILING]

197
00:14:48,899 --> 00:14:51,970
We can't let it cross the bridge
into the city!

198
00:14:52,004 --> 00:14:52,805
What's its current location?

199
00:14:52,838 --> 00:14:55,375
It's heading towards us,
underground!

200
00:14:55,409 --> 00:14:56,711
TAWASHI:
Underground?

201
00:15:01,417 --> 00:15:02,920
[GRUNTS, SCREAMS]

202
00:15:05,657 --> 00:15:06,591
Fire!

203
00:15:10,697 --> 00:15:12,800
Destroy it! Aim! Fire!

204
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,876
Their weapons
aren't making a scratch.

205
00:15:18,909 --> 00:15:22,013
Magnamite's just absorbing
more energy.

206
00:15:22,048 --> 00:15:23,450
But that means...

207
00:15:25,052 --> 00:15:28,457
Don't stop. Keep going. More!

208
00:15:31,061 --> 00:15:32,463
MAN:
Run!

209
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:36,702
MAN 2:
Run!

210
00:15:45,615 --> 00:15:48,452
This is your last warning.
Now, cool your jets or else.

211
00:15:56,631 --> 00:15:57,565
Fall back!

212
00:16:00,236 --> 00:16:01,038
Huh?

213
00:16:09,650 --> 00:16:10,652
Astro!

214
00:16:19,131 --> 00:16:20,132
Huh?

215
00:16:21,601 --> 00:16:22,836
<i>Tobio.</i>

216
00:16:27,043 --> 00:16:27,977
Astro!

217
00:16:30,714 --> 00:16:33,718
TAWASHI:
Get ready to fire again.

218
00:16:33,752 --> 00:16:36,122
Aim for the center
of its power core.

219
00:16:36,156 --> 00:16:37,190
No, wait.
You don't understand.

220
00:16:40,027 --> 00:16:41,830
First position. Get ready!

221
00:16:44,301 --> 00:16:45,269
Don't shoot!

222
00:16:45,302 --> 00:16:45,936
Take aim.

223
00:16:49,676 --> 00:16:51,244
If you fire at Magnamite again,

224
00:16:51,278 --> 00:16:53,614
it could set off
a massive explosion!

225
00:16:58,755 --> 00:17:00,224
Impossible!

226
00:17:00,257 --> 00:17:01,526
Astro?

227
00:17:01,559 --> 00:17:03,962
[♪]

228
00:17:13,043 --> 00:17:14,946
That flying kid saved us.

229
00:17:14,979 --> 00:17:15,914
Awesome!

230
00:17:22,924 --> 00:17:24,993
Dr. O'Shay was right.

231
00:17:25,027 --> 00:17:27,196
<i>He is amazing.</i>

232
00:17:31,336 --> 00:17:34,607
[MAGNAMITE GROANING]

233
00:17:34,641 --> 00:17:35,943
What's that?

234
00:17:38,046 --> 00:17:40,250
Are you hurt?

235
00:17:44,155 --> 00:17:46,324
Too much energy!

236
00:17:48,327 --> 00:17:50,731
Too much energy?

237
00:17:50,765 --> 00:17:53,669
I get it!
You're overloaded!

238
00:17:53,702 --> 00:17:56,139
You need to release
some of that energy.

239
00:18:00,011 --> 00:18:01,881
Astro. What's happening?

240
00:18:03,283 --> 00:18:06,053
I've got a plan.
Give some to me.

241
00:18:12,430 --> 00:18:13,364
Ready!

242
00:18:24,948 --> 00:18:26,650
O'SHAY:
All that energy.

243
00:18:26,683 --> 00:18:30,022
He has no way of knowing
if his body can take it.

244
00:18:38,835 --> 00:18:41,739
Phew. You rest, I'll drive.

245
00:18:45,144 --> 00:18:46,279
What happened?

246
00:18:47,113 --> 00:18:48,783
It's incredible.

247
00:18:56,261 --> 00:18:58,063
Magnamite is returning.

248
00:18:58,096 --> 00:19:01,368
I don't believe it.
Well, prepare for reattachment.

249
00:19:12,217 --> 00:19:14,220
Reboot the system.

250
00:19:17,224 --> 00:19:20,362
Magnamite, next time
you're overly energetic,

251
00:19:20,396 --> 00:19:23,066
just give me a shout.

252
00:19:23,100 --> 00:19:24,368
ADMINISTRATOR:
System's back to normal.

253
00:19:24,402 --> 00:19:26,070
Okay, see you later.

254
00:19:26,104 --> 00:19:27,707
MAGNAMITE:
Thank you.

255
00:19:42,829 --> 00:19:44,832
Of course!

256
00:19:44,865 --> 00:19:47,135
His body is releasing
the excess energy as light.

257
00:19:47,168 --> 00:19:48,102
Genius!

258
00:19:51,808 --> 00:19:54,446
It's beautiful,
like a shooting star.

259
00:19:58,217 --> 00:20:00,320
Astro, are you okay?

260
00:20:00,354 --> 00:20:03,024
Hi there, doctor!

261
